A LOT of changes in this update, and many of them without prior PTS testing apparently.<br>Many of these new implants have a lot of potential, some may even be highly mandatory (Bionics looks amazing for engineers, Fortify might be a gamechanger for drops on points).<br><br>Negative: they removed the Orders channel, for no discernable reason it seems. No real alternative, effectively crippling faction coordination ingame.<br><br>Slight HESH nerf and AP buff, and finally tank guns will kill Flak armour infanty on a direct hit. Nothing quite so tilting as hitting a HA to the face with an FPC and not getting a kill.<br><br>The implant crafting system will be largely irrelevant for seasoned players, most of the interesting ones are exceptionals and cannot be crafted, the rest will be gotten simply through alerts.<br><br>Looking forward to seeing these *ahem* "code improvements" in practice.<br><br><br>Fyi:<br><a href="https://i.imgur.com/tMzrdR3.png" class="postlink">https://i.imgur.com/tMzrdR3.png</a><br><br>New implant drop rates. TL;DR: ISO4-Recyclers all the way to obtain the exceptional/uncommon ones asap.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://www.emeraldimmersion.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=103">Mardevian</a> — Thu Aug 16, 2018 3:05 pm</p><hr />
